 the women's event where the winning move came inside 4km to go.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your newsletter sign-up\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"two thrilling road races\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's event\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"the winning move\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 503}, {\"ngram\": \"4km\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The open, dynamic racing comes partly due to the small team sizes but mostly because there are no race radios so riders have to figure out what to do on their own.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The open, dynamic racing\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"the small team\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"sizes\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"no race radios\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The radio debate is due to fire up again as the UCI introduces another test of race radio restrictions, first at theVuelta a Burgosbeginning on Monday and during three stages of the Tour de Pologne (12-18 August).\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 742, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.933247070439788e-14, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}, {\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Pologne\", \"score\": 0.9999999999140528, \"rank\": 6.601572289725268e-11, \"text\": \"Tour de Pologne\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Pologne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Pologne\"}], \"nou