ay\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medalist Kristin Faulkner(USA) and silver medalist Marianne Vos (Netherlands) agreed.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1302, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristin_Halvorsen\", \"score\": 0.9998580424828041, \"rank\": 9.242641212119726e-05, \"text\": \"Kristin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristin_Halvorsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristin_Halvorsen\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999990027391, \"rank\": 9.973650878681865e-10, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9937918599800228, \"rank\": 0.006246845123459473, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marianne Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999980472349275, \"rank\": 1.81360980505656e-06, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When you do not have radios, I think it falls a lot more on the riders to have race tactics and race intuition,\\\" Faulkner said.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999999990027391, \"rank\": 9.973650878681865e-10, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"radios\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"race tactics\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"race intuition\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think you really have to pay a lot more attention to what every single rider is doing, how tired they are, what the team tactics are, who's riding for who, who's taking bottles for who.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot more attention\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1561}, {\"ngram\": \"every single rider\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the team tactics\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"bottles\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I like it.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's more fun, and I think it adds a much more intellectual game to what's happening.\\\"\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more fun\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1732}, {\"ngram\": \"a much more intellectual game\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The latest race content\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"interviews\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"features\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"reviews\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1861}, {\"ngram\": \"expert buying guides\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vos said she did not think not having radios changed much.\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"radios\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1955}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it's true, you have to pay attention mostly, and you have to think on your own, so that makes it interesting.\\\"\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Professional cycling has struggled with the race radio debate for more than a decade, as opponents say they make racing boring, and predictable and turn riders into robots.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Professional cycling\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2107}, {\"ngram\": \"the race radio debate\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2148}, {\"ngram\": \"more than a decade\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"opponents\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2185}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2246}, {\"ngram\": \"robots\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UCI tried to ban them in 2010, beginning with lower-level races but the WorldTour teams threatened boycotts and successfully defended their use, citing rider safety concerns.\", \"from\": 2260, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.933247070439788e-14, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"lower-level races\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2327}, {\"ngram\": \"the WorldTour teams\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2351}, {\"ngram\": \"boycotts\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2371}, {\"ngram\": \"their use\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"rider safety concerns\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams have used the safety angle to keep radio communication open.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teams\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety angle\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2472}, {\"ngram\": \"radio communication\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dutch Rabobank team claimed radios saved the life of Pedro Horrillo when he crashed into a ravine at the 2009 Giro d'Italia, saying if teammate Jos van Emden had not been able to immediately call to inform them of the crash, Horrillo might never have lost his life.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.8216632358968599, \"rank\": 0.2106392282613761, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Horrillo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pedro Horrillo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Horrillo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pedro_Horrillo\"}, {\"begin\": 2621, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 0.9582059079478303, \"rank\": 0.043616904142606626, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_Giro_d'Italia\"}, {\"begin\": 2655, \"end\": 2668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos_van_Emden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jos van Emden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos_van_Emden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jos_van_Emden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"radios\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"the life\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2560}, {\"ngram\": \"a ravine\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"the crash\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2734}, {\"ngram\": \"Horrillo\", \"from\": 2736, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2775}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other side of the debate is a more esoteric basis in favour of banning radios.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2863, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 2781, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"the debate\", \"from\": 2799, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"a more esoteric basis\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2844}, {\"ngram\": \"banning radios\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French teams, who are steeped in cycling's history and have a culture that embraces the panache and self-driven aspects of the sport, have said\\\"The security argument is a fraud\\\"and the constant push from directors for riders to move up before critical points cause more safety problems than radios solve.\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 3168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2864, \"end\": 2870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8931453204758021, \"rank\": 0.11918046804254331, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cycling's history\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2914}, {\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"the panache\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2959}, {\"ngram\": \"self-driven aspects\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2996}, {\"ngram\": \"said\\\"The security argument\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"a fraud\\\"and the constant push\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3062}, {\"ngram\": \"directors\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3077}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3088}, {\"ngram\": \"critical points\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"more safety problems\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3149}, {\"ngram\": \"radios\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even a ban on radios might not have the intended effect, as teams in pro races are large enough to have riders shuttling back and forth from team cars to get information and strategy advice.\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3364, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even a ban\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3184}, {\"ngram\": \"radios\", \"from\": 3188, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"the intended effect\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3229}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3239}, {\"ngram\": \"pro races\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3252}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3284}, {\"ngram\": \"team cars\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3324}, {\"ngram\": \"information and strategy advice\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Part of the appeal of the Olympics is the quirky mix of small teams, riders from outside the normal pro peloton and smaller peloton.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3498, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Part\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3370}, {\"ngram\": \"the appeal\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3384}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3400}, {\"ngram\": \"the quirky mix\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3418}, {\"ngram\": \"small teams\", \"from\": 3422, \"